            "description": "DMI notice about IELTS exam format rumours and how students should follow official updates.",
            "article_body": "# Notification: About Alleged IELTS Exam 2026 Format Update\n\nDear DMI IELTS Students,\n\nYou may see messages online claiming that the IELTS exam format has changed for 2026. Please do not depend on rumours, forwarded posts, or unofficial social media updates.\n\n## DMI Guidance\n\n- IELTS format changes should be accepted only when they are announced by official IELTS organisations such as the British Council, IDP, Cambridge English, or IELTS.org.\n- DMI Computer Education will update students if any confirmed IELTS format change affects classroom practice, LMS practice, or mock tests.\n- Until an official change is confirmed, continue practising the current IELTS Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking format.\n\n## What Students Should Do\n\n- Follow your DMI teacher's instructions.\n- Practise with the current test format in this LMS.\n- Check official IELTS sources before believing any online claim.\n- Ask DMI staff if you are unsure about a message you received.\n\nDMI IELTS Department\nDMI Computer Education",
